{"word":"ὀρχηστύς","slug":"ὀρχηστύς","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ὀρχηστύς</b></el> <el>(ὀρχηστύς, ύος, ἡ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>ionic for <a href='S:ὄρχησις'><el>ὄρχησις</el></a>\n<p/><i>the dance</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:contracted, contraction'>contr.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a> <el>ὀρχηστυῖ</el> <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>ῡ</el> in <a href='S:nominative'>nom.</a> and <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a>\n"}]}